Yobe State Governor Ibrahim Gaidam has approved the recruitment of three professors and two PhD holders from Egypt and 30 Nigerians into the newly established College of Medical Sciences of the Yobe State University, Damaturu. A statement by the Director-General, Press Affairs to the state governor, Malam Abdullahi Bego, said the employment of the additional personnel was on permanent and pensionable as well as sabbatical basis. According to the statement, the recruitments cover both academic and non-academic cadres of the college and will ensure its smooth take-off. Bego also said among those recruited were professor of human physiology, 18 graduate assistants, and 11 laboratory technologists and assistant laboratory technologists. The governor had earlier approved the appointment of a provost for the college.